Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: Correct me if im way off but... the DAPP used to do the ARRR sprout to sapling conversions... it did almost exactly what you are talking about for this vote thing just it had to be done due to ARRR not supporting t addresses. So, the process of voting you described seems to use some of the same steps... coin V is sent via z transaction to NN voters so thats obscured. DAPP can be adapted to perform w/e path of steps you want to vote...  but will limit any other functions other than sending to the vote addresses. Guarantees no one screws it up.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: and to follow that, NN ops should be required to vote at all times no? Continued missing votes could be another item added to the list a reasons to HF and remove NN pubkeys as new slots open up.
